# display: the manual's Started/Stopped worked example (display.md "Showing texts").
# A button (default toggle: each rising edge flips its output) drives
# _RUNNING / _NOT_RUNNING (inverted).  Two display circuits each gate a text by
# one of the cables.  A display sends an update only when its text CHANGES and is
# non-empty: when a text multiplies out to 0 (empty) that circuit stays quiet and
# the OTHER circuit, whose text just returned from empty to its slot number, wins
# the screen.  Default linger (0.01 s = 1 tick here) has expired by the time the
# other circuit changes, so hand-off is clean.  Each toggle needs its own rising
# edge, so the button is pressed (0->1), released (1->0), then pressed again.
tickrate 100
patch <<<
[db8e]
[p2b8]

[button]
    button   = B2.1
    output   = _RUNNING
    inverted = _NOT_RUNNING

[display]
    text = "Started" * _RUNNING

[display]
    text = "Stopped" * _NOT_RUNNING
>>>
@0 expectdisplay D1 text "Stopped"
@2 set B2.1 1
@2 expectdisplay D1 text "Started"
@3 set B2.1 0
@4 set B2.1 1
@4 expectdisplay D1 text "Stopped"
